					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Absor on Test Server Changes</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=359212" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Some issues were recently brought up about the Test Server changes on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/054905.html">forums</a> today:
<blockquote>
<p>
-Dr wrote:</p>
<p>
<i>>"the new D&D rules are totally lame. Mages in plate armour? bah just plane silly"<</i></p>
<p>
<b>And, oddly enough, it was the D&D rules that first made us all think that spell casters should not be able to wear armor…</b></p>
<p>
<b>The changes you see on test are not in any way going to make warriors obsolete. They will still have the best defense and offensive power (when compared to the hybrids). They will still have a significant hit point advantage. They will still have the best armor and weapons, and the greatest versatility in equipment.</b></p>
<p>
<b>Also, the changes you see are not likely to be the last. They were generated from the talks we've been having, and they were the most obvious changes to address the hybrid classes. We are not done evaluating things, as should be obvious by the fact that I've only just opened the last to hybrid talks today.</b></p>
<p>
Slackjaw wrote:</p>
<p>
<i>>"The thing that _does_ bother me, in reflection, is that aside from fixing a bug with 2 disciplines, it appears that the other warrior concerns were deemed inappropriate."<</i></p>
<p>
<b>My comments above apply to all classes. These are just the immediate and obvious changes. We have not delved into the entirety of class balance, and we haven't even finished all the talks.</b></p>
<p>
<b>Let's not jump the gun here.</b></p>
<p>
<b>Alan</b></p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
