	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Most of what I have learned about this game has been through watching others play, and reading reading and reading some more on the web pages. When I finally began to play, I felt very well equipped to develop a strong character. First I was a magician, but tired of that, and created a Barbarian Shaman. I totally love the character and seldon pull out my original Erudite Magician. <BR>
<BR>
What I have learned, first in reading and watching, and then in actual experience, is that the world of Everquest is best lived enjoyed in a group. Together in a party, if organized and well led, amazing things can happen. All of our characters have innate abilities and strengths we can bring to make the most out of our fellow party members. We have weaknesses, all of us, one thing or another, but generally, there is something to offset that. Let me address the Wizard armor. Yes, they can only wear certain types of robes. But they are not called &quot;nukers&quot; for nothing.<BR>
<BR>
There are drawbacks to every class, and everyone wants their class to be all powerful and without weaknesses. As a Shaman, I would love to have nukes, but I understand that my character is an all around character, maybe not as strong in any one thing as others are, but I can buff, I can fight, I can de-buff, and I can heal. Played right and organized, I can be a very effective member in a party. I know there are many who gripe about this buff, and that heal spell. But I chose my character for the challenge, and will play the best I can with what strengths AND weakness I have and have a good time. <BR>
<BR>
If there are plans to improve one classes' weakness, then ALL classes should get an equal perk to keep things level. Give something to all or nothing at all. Either way, I will be playing and having a great time. <BR>
<BR>
PS my only gripe is that my spells are becoming increasingly hard to find while other casters don't seem to struggle so much. I am however looking on the bright side, and figure it builds character to run across the world for 1 measly spell. :P<BR>
<BR>
Whytspirit of Halas<BR>
Powers of Fate<BR>
Quellious
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
